Gallanza of the Silver Wolf Corps

's crew exits the Grim Basin and arrives
in the beautiful blue skies of Zegagrande. The
peaceful moment is shattered by ambushing wyverns.
 and Lyria summon Bahamut, but the primal
beast begins acting up.

The crew quells Bahamut's rampage, but Lyria loses
consciousness and falls off the airship. 
grabs her but soon tumbles after.  wakes
up in an unknown forest and starts searching for
Lyria.

Rolan, a local handyman, heads for Tempeal to calm
a primal beast gone mad. The crew go with him,
thinking they might discover clues as to why
Bahamut went berserk. Meanwhile, goblins are
running amok in Tempeal, adding to the chaos.

Furycane, the primal beast of vitality, rampages
within Tempeal's mines. The crew battles its
fierce winds and manage to appease the agitated
primal. Soon after, they are confronted by Lilith
and her Pilgrims of Avia.

After Lyria's kidnapping, the crew chases after
Lilith's flagship, the Ameretat. A battle soon
ensues with Avia's fleet. The crew manages to get
past the blockade of ships, but then they have to
contend with Gallanza, one of Avia's generals.

The damaged Grandcypher is forced to make an
emergency landing on Mt. Neigelith. Rolan's
friend, a mystic living on the mountain, can help
them, but the crew must go on foot to find her.
Monsters and Avia obstruct them as they climb.

The church is using a forbidden implement called a
mind sealer to brainwash Lyria. The crew go to
Seedhollow to meet an info broker named Zathba. He
knows how to release the mind sealer but wants the
crew to investigate some ruins in exchange.

After obtaining the catalyst to free Lyria from
the mind sealer, the crew tracks Avia to Phondam
and find Lyria imprisoned in a crystal atop Vulkan
Bolla, the primal beast of dread. The crew and Id
join forces and pursue the primal to save Lyria.

Rolan reveals the full truth, including Lilith's
plan to open a gate using Angra Mainyu's power,
which would obliterate Zegagrande in the process.
For the future of this skydom, the crew returns to
Seedhollow to stop Avia.

Losing her only means of reaching the Astral
Realm, Lilith sacrifices Zegagrande's primal
beasts to raise the Pillar of Vayoi, an island of
twisted energy. Now that the crew has rescued
Lyria, they head to Vayoi to stop Lilith once and
for all.

Despite fusing with Angra Mainyu, Lilith is
defeated by Id and the crew. However, a desperate
Lilith releases Bahamut from within Id, causing
him to transform into Bahamut Versa. He flies off,
and the crew gives chase for the sake of the Sky
Realm.

Thanks to Rolan's sacrifice, Id and the crew return 
to Folca safely. Id vows to continue Rolan's role as 
Folca's Mr. Fix It. Luckily for him,  and the 
others are more than happy to help him get acclimated 
to his newfound purpose.
